        ban - Bans the use of specific functions or global methods.
        ban-comma-operator - Disallows the comma operator to be used.
        ban-types - Bans specific types from being used. Does not ban the corresponding runtime objects from being used.
    V   binary-expression-operand-order - In a binary expression, a literal should always be on the right-hand side if possible. For example, prefer ‘x + 1’ over ‘1 + x’.
v   V   callable-types - An interface or literal type with just a call signature can be written as a function type.
v   V   class-name - Enforces PascalCased class and interface names.
v   V   comment-format - Enforces formatting rules for single-line comments.
        completed-docs - Enforces JSDoc comments for important items be filled out.
v       curly - Enforces braces for if/for/do/while statements.
    V   cyclomatic-complexity - Enforces a threshold of cyclomatic complexity.
v       deprecation - Warns when deprecated APIs are used.
    V   encoding - Enforces UTF-8 file encoding.
v   V   eofline - Ensures the file ends with a newline.
        file-header - Enforces a certain header comment for all files, matched by a regular expression.
    V   >>> file-name-casing - Enforces a consistent file naming convention
v   V   forin - Requires a for ... in statement to be filtered with an if statement.
